WEBVTT

00:06.214 --> 00:08.381
We are gonna have ourselves
an adventure, right?

00:08.464 --> 00:09.756
Just us three.

00:11.339 --> 00:13.464
-Mom?
-It's great, isn't it?

00:14.089 --> 00:16.422
♪ (OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYS) ♪

00:17.422 --> 00:20.089
-ALAN: Can I help you?
-I'm booked to stay here today.

00:20.422 --> 00:22.798
-I'm afraid it's not possible.
-What?

00:23.923 --> 00:26.756
This place,
why's it so important to you?

00:27.214 --> 00:29.214
HELEN:
<i>My girls have been through</i>
<i>a lot.</i>

00:29.422 --> 00:30.923
I want them to feel good.

00:31.881 --> 00:33.089
Then leave.

00:33.923 --> 00:35.130
HELEN: <i>What's going on?</i>

00:35.381 --> 00:37.422
Everyone here's acting like
something bad's gonna happen.

00:37.714 --> 00:39.589
<i>I was at that shoreside place.</i>

00:40.297 --> 00:42.214
We've got a woman in labor
on OC.

00:42.464 --> 00:44.589
<i>What you saw</i>
<i>was just medical equipment.</i>

00:44.923 --> 00:46.756
I saw something else
in that place.

00:47.589 --> 00:49.506
MRS. MARTIN: <i>We've had</i>
<i>our customs for years,</i>

00:49.798 --> 00:51.756
<i>but I'm not apologizing</i>
<i>for 'em.</i>

00:52.464 --> 00:53.714
So, we're safe here then?

00:53.798 --> 00:55.464
Yeah, we can give you a room.

00:56.130 --> 00:58.172
Are we going home
in the morning, Mom?

00:58.255 --> 01:02.297
We'll see, baby.
But now, we sleep.

01:03.339 --> 01:04.673
♪ (MUSIC CONCLUDES) ♪

01:24.214 --> 01:27.297
♪ ♪

01:54.839 --> 01:57.881
(gentle snoring)

02:00.673 --> 02:02.172
(heartbeat)

02:06.172 --> 02:07.631
Sam:
<i>Cass!</i>

02:07.714 --> 02:09.839
(sighs)

02:10.506 --> 02:13.297
(car approaches)

02:13.381 --> 02:15.881
-(car door opens)
-(woman screaming)

02:18.714 --> 02:21.255
(footsteps)

02:22.381 --> 02:24.798
-(thud)
-W-what was that?

02:24.881 --> 02:26.422
-(clattering)
-Mom?

02:26.506 --> 02:28.047
-(bang)
-(Talulah gasps)

02:28.881 --> 02:32.464
-(woman screaming)
-(all gasp)

02:32.547 --> 02:33.547
Stay there.

02:34.422 --> 02:36.547
Talulah:
Don't go out there.

02:37.047 --> 02:39.005
Helen:
Stay there, okay?

02:39.089 --> 02:41.172
Do not move.

02:43.089 --> 02:44.464
(opens door)

02:44.547 --> 02:47.464
(indistinct arguing)

02:47.547 --> 02:48.923
(door shuts)

02:50.756 --> 02:52.964
(tense music playing)

02:53.047 --> 02:54.589
♪ ♪

02:55.923 --> 02:58.547
(muffled arguing)

03:01.422 --> 03:03.589
(woman screaming)

03:07.589 --> 03:10.172
(arguing continues)

03:10.255 --> 03:12.297
(woman screaming)

03:14.589 --> 03:17.631
-Preacher: Can we talk?!
Can we talk?!
-(overlapping yelling)

03:19.297 --> 03:21.798
(woman screaming)

03:24.214 --> 03:27.964
-(yelling continues)
-(woman screaming)

03:29.255 --> 03:31.839
Can we please
all just calm down?
Can we talk!

03:31.923 --> 03:33.881
-Man: Shut up!
-Can we talk?! Please!

03:33.964 --> 03:36.589
(arguing continues)

03:37.923 --> 03:40.964
(overlapping chatter,
indistinct)

03:45.297 --> 03:47.089
Mrs. Martin:
She doesn't want my help!

03:47.172 --> 03:48.881
-(arguing)
-You're a killer!
Don't let her near me!

03:48.964 --> 03:51.381
I don't want her to touch me!

03:51.464 --> 03:54.005
-Okay, okay, okay, okay!
-(screaming)

03:54.089 --> 03:55.881
Alright, Jess!
Alright, alright, alright!

03:55.964 --> 03:59.214
♪ ♪

03:59.297 --> 04:00.714
Fucking pointing
a gun at people, eh?

04:00.798 --> 04:02.422
You got it in you to
use that, have you?

04:02.506 --> 04:04.422
-Well, I just might. Come on.
-Cowboy: Calm down.

04:04.506 --> 04:06.506
Larry:
You want to calm the fuck
out of that fucking door, mate.

04:06.589 --> 04:09.631
-Then we can talk about
calming the fuck down.
-Jason: You need to help her.

04:10.839 --> 04:12.422
That child is one of us.

04:12.631 --> 04:14.255
You know how much it matters.

04:14.798 --> 04:16.756
Mrs. Martin:
So we're a community
again, are we?

04:16.839 --> 04:19.798
How cunting lovely
for us all.

04:19.881 --> 04:22.464
(Jess panting)

04:22.547 --> 04:24.422
-No! No, not her! Not her!
-Jason: It's alright! Alright!

04:24.506 --> 04:27.339
(indistinct yelling)

04:29.214 --> 04:32.297
(fire crackling)

04:34.506 --> 04:36.130
He's, uh,
lying wrong...

04:36.214 --> 04:37.714
He-he-he's crossways.

04:38.172 --> 04:39.422
What are you sayin'?

04:39.506 --> 04:41.881
I'm saying,
it's, it's trans...

04:41.964 --> 04:43.506
fucking thing is...

04:44.214 --> 04:46.756
He's across her pelvis,
and she can't get him out.

04:46.839 --> 04:48.881
Well, you can do
something, right?

04:48.964 --> 04:50.547
I'm not
a shitting doctor!

04:50.631 --> 04:52.464
Mrs. Martin:
You never should've let
her stay on the island!

04:52.547 --> 04:54.089
-I told you that!
-Larry: That's what this is!

04:54.172 --> 04:56.422
They're trying to take
her off the island, Jay!

04:56.506 --> 04:58.839
Larry, you were
stupid as a boy,

04:58.923 --> 05:01.547
-but you border on
moronic as an adult.
-Larry: Listen, cunt.

05:02.172 --> 05:05.005
You help her,
or it won't just be her blood
on this floor tonight.

05:05.089 --> 05:07.089
(muffled)

05:07.172 --> 05:09.631
Mr. Martin:
Don't you talk to
my wife like that, alright?

05:09.714 --> 05:10.964
(sighs)

05:11.047 --> 05:14.047
(muffled arguing continues)

05:17.005 --> 05:18.255
(sighs)

05:21.547 --> 05:23.589
♪ ♪

05:35.714 --> 05:37.214
Sam:
<i>Cass!</i>

05:41.089 --> 05:44.130
(Jess screaming)

05:52.964 --> 05:54.089
(sniffles)

05:55.422 --> 05:58.047
-(opens door)
-Mrs. Martin: We have
a medic here, get him!

05:58.130 --> 06:01.172
Jason:
Janny's passed out drunk.
We're alone here.

06:01.255 --> 06:03.339
Well, you should've thought
of that before you closed

06:03.422 --> 06:05.839
-the island down!
-Let me look.

06:05.923 --> 06:08.255
(arguing stops)

06:09.214 --> 06:10.547
I can help.

06:10.631 --> 06:11.923
Are you a doctor?

06:12.756 --> 06:15.172
No, but I...
I used to be a vet.

06:15.255 --> 06:17.297
Larry:
A fucking vet?

06:17.381 --> 06:19.381
-You "used to be a vet"?
-Helen: Look,

06:19.464 --> 06:21.714
-she needs help now.
-(Jess whimpering)

06:21.798 --> 06:24.047
She should be in a hospital
but you can't get her to one.

06:24.130 --> 06:26.381
She could die.
They both could die.

06:26.464 --> 06:28.631
So I'm the best
hope you've got.

06:29.631 --> 06:31.506
This is going nowhere, Jay.

06:31.589 --> 06:33.964
-(Jess groaning)
-Jason: Save her.

06:34.756 --> 06:36.506
-Save 'em both.
-(groaning)

06:36.589 --> 06:39.297
-(fire crackling)
-(sighs)

06:44.422 --> 06:46.381
(Jess whimpering)

06:46.464 --> 06:48.547
-What's your name, hon?
-I'm Jess.

06:48.631 --> 06:50.547
Jess, I'd like to have a look

06:50.631 --> 06:52.881
-and see what's going on.
Is that okay?
-Uh-huh.

06:52.964 --> 06:54.422
Helen:
Alright. Can I get
you on your back?

06:54.506 --> 06:56.130
-(groans)
-Yeah? Okay?

06:57.631 --> 06:59.214
Thank you.

06:59.297 --> 07:02.547
Jason:
There we are, Jess.
Alright. There we are.

07:02.631 --> 07:04.673
(groaning)

07:08.172 --> 07:09.422
-(sighs)
-Excuse me?

07:09.506 --> 07:10.756
(Jess whimpers)

07:10.839 --> 07:12.047
Oh, yeah, sorry.

07:12.130 --> 07:14.172
(murmuring)

07:20.798 --> 07:23.923
(tense music playing)

07:24.005 --> 07:26.005
♪ ♪

07:39.172 --> 07:40.673
(grunting)

07:41.881 --> 07:44.839
Yeah, she's right.
It's a transverse lie.

07:45.547 --> 07:47.589
Can you get me
some flour, please?

07:48.714 --> 07:50.255
Have your waters
broken yet, Jess?

07:51.381 --> 07:54.214
Okay. Well, that's good,
that's really good news.

07:54.923 --> 07:56.631
And is this your first?

07:56.714 --> 07:58.589
No, I have two girls.

07:58.673 --> 08:00.798
Alright. Good.

08:00.881 --> 08:02.506
Then you've
totally got this.

08:02.589 --> 08:04.464
I'm just gonna keep
you on your back,

08:04.547 --> 08:06.881
and I'm gonna turn
your baby, okay?

08:08.172 --> 08:10.506
You can do that?

08:11.881 --> 08:13.130
Yeah, I can.

08:13.214 --> 08:15.881
It's gonna surprise you,
and you will feel it.

08:16.881 --> 08:18.047
(sighs)

08:18.714 --> 08:21.130
(rubbing hands)

08:21.214 --> 08:24.214
♪ ♪

08:28.422 --> 08:29.756
Okay.

08:36.214 --> 08:38.756
(groaning)

08:41.714 --> 08:42.964
(sighs)

08:45.381 --> 08:48.422
(painful groaning)

08:50.089 --> 08:52.631
(groans)

08:55.923 --> 08:59.089
(ragged breathing)

09:02.047 --> 09:03.297
(sighs)

09:05.297 --> 09:08.422
(groaning)

09:09.756 --> 09:10.714
(sighs)

09:10.798 --> 09:13.881
(heavy breathing)

09:13.964 --> 09:15.339
(groans)

09:16.172 --> 09:17.255
(sighs)

09:19.756 --> 09:21.297
-(sighs)
-(Jess groans)

09:24.130 --> 09:25.714
Okay.

09:25.798 --> 09:28.047
Okay. Alright.

09:28.130 --> 09:29.381
(sighs)

09:29.464 --> 09:32.881
He's in the perfect
position now. (laughs)

09:32.964 --> 09:35.172
-(groaning)
-(sighs)

09:35.255 --> 09:38.464
-Helen: We've done it.
We've done it.
-(groans)

09:39.589 --> 09:42.506
Alright. I can-- I can
feel a contraction coming,

09:42.589 --> 09:43.923
so I'm just gonna stay here.

09:44.005 --> 09:45.214
(groaning)

09:45.297 --> 09:48.422
Helen (muffled):
Okay. Here we go.
Here we go. It's okay.

09:49.464 --> 09:51.673
-(Jess groaning)
-Just go with it...

09:52.714 --> 09:53.923
Talulah:
What's going on?

09:54.005 --> 09:55.714
Is she having a baby?

09:55.798 --> 09:58.589
-I wanna see it come out!
-Stop it, Lu.

09:58.673 --> 10:01.589
Ellie:
There's not enough room.
Just go to bed.

10:01.673 --> 10:03.589
If Mom sees you down here,
I'll get into real trouble.

10:03.673 --> 10:06.547
-So will I.
-No, you won't.

10:06.631 --> 10:08.714
You never do.
You get away with everything

10:08.798 --> 10:10.631
because you're her
little favorite.

10:10.714 --> 10:12.798
Oh, fuck off, Ellie.

10:16.964 --> 10:19.422
Anyway, you're Dad's favorite,

10:19.506 --> 10:22.464
and by the way, he ran off
because he's a psycho,

10:22.547 --> 10:23.673
just like you.

10:24.798 --> 10:26.964
-Don't say that.
-Why?

10:27.631 --> 10:30.464
Who you gonna tell?
Can't tell Mom.

10:30.714 --> 10:33.673
Why don't you tell God? I mean,

10:33.756 --> 10:35.964
he's your best mate after all.

10:36.047 --> 10:37.464
Kail:
Then she's lucky.

10:37.547 --> 10:38.964
♪ ♪

10:39.047 --> 10:41.255
Person who has God on their side

10:41.339 --> 10:43.297
is not a person to mess with.

10:43.381 --> 10:46.381
Talulah:
Yeah, well,
I don't believe in God.

10:47.214 --> 10:50.047
"I don't believe in God..."

10:52.047 --> 10:53.339
Do you know why you don't?

10:54.589 --> 10:58.005
Because you're
a little... sheep.

10:58.339 --> 10:59.506
I'm not a sheep.

10:59.589 --> 11:01.923
Kail:
A little sheep who goes along

11:02.005 --> 11:04.297
with all her little friends,

11:04.381 --> 11:06.297
wearing the same clothes,

11:06.381 --> 11:09.339
swapping Pokémons, and...

11:09.422 --> 11:11.964
looking at stupid
little screens.

11:12.047 --> 11:14.089
But do you know what
happens to sheep?

11:17.047 --> 11:18.339
They get slaughtered.

11:18.422 --> 11:21.756
-(Talulah gasps)
-So the rest of us can feed.

11:22.631 --> 11:24.673
Off to bed now, sheepy.

11:24.756 --> 11:27.506
Yeah, well, I'm telling Mom.

11:27.589 --> 11:29.589
(running footsteps)

11:30.422 --> 11:31.297
(door shuts)

11:32.506 --> 11:35.339
-(panting)
-Alright. This is
just normal labor now.

11:35.422 --> 11:37.339
I don't want them
to take me away.

11:37.422 --> 11:39.130
No one's taking
you anywhere, hon.

11:39.214 --> 11:40.798
You just tell me
what you need.

11:40.881 --> 11:43.839
-Dark, small, no people...
-Mm-hmm.

11:43.923 --> 11:46.839
Oh, there's a...
there's a bathroom back there.

11:46.923 --> 11:48.506
Okay.
Let's get you inside.

11:48.589 --> 11:50.089
Come on.

11:51.881 --> 11:54.047
-(Jess whimpering)
-Here we go.

11:54.130 --> 11:57.172
Mrs. Martin:
Get some cushions.
There's a bed spread upstairs.

11:57.255 --> 11:58.756
(indistinct chatter)

11:58.839 --> 12:00.881
-Mrs. Martin:
It's on the chair.
-(indistinct chatter)

12:00.964 --> 12:02.756
Mrs. Martin:
It's a fucking bathroom...

12:02.839 --> 12:05.464
It's okay. Alright.

12:06.631 --> 12:09.547
They're bringing
stuff to make it nice.

12:09.631 --> 12:11.130
What do you need now?

12:11.964 --> 12:13.464
I wanna be alone.

12:14.673 --> 12:17.673
-(sighs)
-No, I-I can't leave
you alone, hon.

12:17.756 --> 12:19.214
(sighs)

12:19.297 --> 12:22.339
Just Jason. Jason can stay.

12:23.506 --> 12:26.005
(muffled chatter)

12:26.089 --> 12:28.964
Alright. Just you
and Jason, yeah?

12:30.089 --> 12:33.047
They'll sort the room
and then you'll be alone.

12:33.130 --> 12:34.881
But I'm gonna be outside,

12:34.964 --> 12:37.297
and if you need anything,
you just say.

12:38.464 --> 12:39.964
Thank you.

12:41.297 --> 12:43.339
This baby is so special.

12:44.506 --> 12:47.339
I didn't ask for this,
but it has come to me.

12:49.547 --> 12:50.964
So, thank you.

12:51.047 --> 12:54.130
♪ ♪

12:56.964 --> 12:58.589
Mrs. Martin:
I suppose you lot of shit fucks

12:58.673 --> 13:01.089
have got no
intention of leaving.

13:01.172 --> 13:03.506
Fucking 10 gallons
of tea it is then.

13:04.047 --> 13:06.631
Don't no one ask for coffee
unless you want it spat in.

13:13.881 --> 13:16.381
The causeway's open if you
were thinking of leaving,

13:17.506 --> 13:19.839
seeing as you're up.

13:25.547 --> 13:28.297
Right, I'm getting
me a smoke.

13:28.381 --> 13:30.589
(indistinct chatter)

13:32.339 --> 13:33.381
(door opens)

13:34.506 --> 13:35.756
-(door shuts)
-(sighs)

13:46.172 --> 13:48.005
(door opens)

13:53.339 --> 13:55.381
Helen:
Can I ask you something?

14:03.881 --> 14:05.589
(door opens)

14:08.756 --> 14:10.839
Thank you.

14:10.923 --> 14:13.172
-For what you just did.
-(sighs)

14:13.255 --> 14:15.673
You saved us from
our own stupidity.

14:15.756 --> 14:17.714
-No, it just...
-No!

14:17.798 --> 14:20.881
You're exactly the right person
at exactly the right time.

14:21.756 --> 14:24.631
Now, if there's anything we
can do for you, anything...

14:27.130 --> 14:29.214
Well actually, there is.

14:32.255 --> 14:35.089
Do you know this man?
He's my husband.

14:35.964 --> 14:38.381
Last year, he went missing.
He just disappeared,

14:38.464 --> 14:40.839
no word, nothing. Just gone.

14:40.923 --> 14:42.589
Missing, eh?

14:42.673 --> 14:45.631
-Did you call the police?
-I did. They weren't
that interested.

14:46.631 --> 14:49.631
Sam has a history
of erratic behavior.
He's done this before.

14:50.923 --> 14:52.422
Never for this long.

14:53.756 --> 14:55.798
What makes you think
he might be here?

14:57.422 --> 15:00.756
'Cause two weeks ago, I got
an email from his account.

15:00.839 --> 15:03.255
It was rambling,
like it was written by a child,

15:03.339 --> 15:05.172
and it said he
was on the island.

15:05.255 --> 15:07.255
Just that. "The island."

15:07.339 --> 15:09.547
And that I should come
and get him before the 14th.

15:09.631 --> 15:12.214
Then yesterday,
I got a call from the police.

15:12.297 --> 15:15.005
They arrested this man,
this corrupt planning officer

15:15.089 --> 15:17.714
in some kind of swoop,
and he told them

15:17.798 --> 15:20.506
that he got a call from Sam
the day he went missing,

15:20.589 --> 15:22.923
and Sam said he
was on "Sea Island."

15:23.005 --> 15:25.130
Sam was near here that day.

15:26.047 --> 15:28.089
It's not Sea Island.

15:28.172 --> 15:29.464
It's Osea Island.

15:30.631 --> 15:31.923
Or Mersea Island.

15:32.005 --> 15:34.756
-Or Northey--
-Please. Have you seen him?

15:34.839 --> 15:36.381
(sighs)

15:36.464 --> 15:39.547
♪ ♪

15:39.631 --> 15:41.297
He hasn't been here.
I'm sorry.

15:41.381 --> 15:44.089
Are you sure?
I mean, it's been a while.
You might not remember.

15:44.172 --> 15:47.172
Good-looking fellow like that?
I'd remember.

15:49.047 --> 15:50.839
I'm sorry, really.

15:53.547 --> 15:54.964
(frustrated sigh)

15:55.047 --> 15:57.422
Do you think it'd be alright
if I asked the others here?

15:57.506 --> 15:59.881
Of course! Of course you can.

16:00.297 --> 16:04.089
But... there's a lot of tension
here tonight. You've seen that.

16:04.172 --> 16:06.756
It's not normal, I promise you.
This is a loving place,

16:06.839 --> 16:10.172
but always best not to
prod tension, I think.

16:13.214 --> 16:15.172
The causeway's open
for another, oh,

16:15.255 --> 16:16.756
hour and 20.

16:17.589 --> 16:19.255
If you can wait,

16:19.339 --> 16:21.464
I could ask around,
discreetly,

16:21.547 --> 16:23.547
and if he's been here,
someone will know.

16:24.673 --> 16:26.923
-Are you sure?
-Sure?

16:27.005 --> 16:28.589
After what you just did?

16:29.881 --> 16:32.005
Show me that
picture again here.

16:32.089 --> 16:34.631
-(shutter snap)
-There we go.

16:34.714 --> 16:35.881
Helen:
Sam is, um,

16:37.047 --> 16:38.964
he's not well.

16:39.047 --> 16:41.506
And his-- his daughters,
they're upstairs, and I just--

16:41.589 --> 16:43.673
You don't have
to explain love.

16:43.756 --> 16:46.798
Never make excuses for love.

16:46.881 --> 16:49.964
♪ ♪

17:06.631 --> 17:08.714
(wind blowing)

17:14.631 --> 17:16.214
Can I have
one of those?

17:20.798 --> 17:22.172
(coughs)

17:22.255 --> 17:24.422
You don't actually
smoke, do you?

17:26.255 --> 17:28.756
-You're not from this place.
-No.

17:31.964 --> 17:33.297
Do you know what's
going on here?

17:35.172 --> 17:37.172
They had this festival.

17:37.964 --> 17:40.255
The hope was that it would
bring people together.

17:42.130 --> 17:43.964
But it did the opposite.

17:44.255 --> 17:45.798
They're divided now,

17:47.422 --> 17:49.506
and they can't find
their way back.

17:50.964 --> 17:52.964
(exhales)

17:53.756 --> 17:56.464
But don't let that make
you think bad about Osea.

17:57.297 --> 17:59.297
This place has a big heart.

18:01.255 --> 18:02.756
And it can heal...

18:04.756 --> 18:06.130
if you let it.

18:07.631 --> 18:09.964
If you need it, Helen.

18:11.005 --> 18:12.547
(door opens)

18:14.631 --> 18:15.798
She's gone!

18:15.881 --> 18:17.631
Jess is flippin' gone!

18:17.714 --> 18:19.881
Helen: Gone? Where?

18:19.964 --> 18:21.923
Wanna see
something cool?

18:22.005 --> 18:24.964
(muffled chatter)

18:25.047 --> 18:27.130
It's from a dig
right here on Osea.

18:27.964 --> 18:29.756
It's a child's finger bone.

18:29.839 --> 18:32.464
That's... awful.

18:35.005 --> 18:37.506
So, what brings you to Osea?

18:39.047 --> 18:41.547
Mom's saying
it's my birthday,

18:41.631 --> 18:43.673
but she's lying.

18:45.172 --> 18:47.506
She doesn't want me to
go back to school yet.

18:48.214 --> 18:49.798
Why?

18:51.631 --> 18:54.714
These girls were
making fun of me.

18:55.547 --> 18:58.255
They always do, but, um,

18:58.714 --> 19:00.673
this time, I hit one.

19:00.756 --> 19:02.839
♪ ♪

19:02.923 --> 19:05.005
That's not so bad.

19:08.422 --> 19:10.506
I was holding a rock.

19:13.714 --> 19:15.089
I didn't even know I had it

19:15.172 --> 19:17.381
until I saw blood
coming out of her eye.

19:18.589 --> 19:22.172
What were they saying?
These girls.

19:23.714 --> 19:25.714
Stuff about my brother.

19:28.714 --> 19:30.214
He was, uh...

19:31.673 --> 19:32.923
murdered.

19:37.923 --> 19:41.464
The ancient Celts
believed that Osea

19:41.547 --> 19:44.005
was the soul of the world.

19:44.089 --> 19:46.923
Means it's the most
important place there is.

19:48.881 --> 19:50.381
If Osea's sick,

19:52.089 --> 19:54.089
the whole planet's sick.

19:56.381 --> 19:58.214
Yeah, but...

19:58.297 --> 20:00.506
that can't be true.

20:00.589 --> 20:02.172
Why not?

20:02.255 --> 20:05.422
Everything's salt
or soil, Ellie.

20:05.756 --> 20:07.631
Hot or cold.

20:07.714 --> 20:09.381
Rain or shine.

20:09.464 --> 20:11.506
Bad or good.

20:11.589 --> 20:15.089
But some years,
it leans too far
one way or the other.

20:16.506 --> 20:19.297
Things are out
of balance...

20:19.923 --> 20:21.881
and bad things happen.

20:21.964 --> 20:25.214
♪ ♪

20:25.297 --> 20:28.172
That thing you did at school?

20:28.255 --> 20:30.756
It's just the balance
gone wrong inside you.

20:30.839 --> 20:33.047
You're not a bad person.

20:33.130 --> 20:34.881
It's just...

20:34.964 --> 20:36.964
you're salt or soil.

20:38.506 --> 20:40.589
Out of whack a little.

20:41.839 --> 20:44.089
But if it's out of whack here,

20:44.172 --> 20:47.172
it affects everything.
Everyone.

20:50.297 --> 20:52.339
There's something on
this island, Ellie.

20:53.506 --> 20:55.589
A place...

20:55.673 --> 20:58.923
so special, no outsider's
ever allowed there.

20:59.005 --> 21:00.839
I could show it to you.

21:01.631 --> 21:02.673
Just you.

21:03.673 --> 21:06.214
Not your mom or your sister.
Just you.

21:08.214 --> 21:09.714
Would you like that?

21:11.464 --> 21:13.214
Yeah.

21:13.297 --> 21:14.798
I would.

21:16.339 --> 21:18.339
I really would.

21:19.214 --> 21:22.839
Crowd:
Jess! Jess! Jess! Jess!

21:23.714 --> 21:26.798
-(yelling continues)
-(creaking)

21:26.881 --> 21:29.047
Yeah,
about your husband...

21:29.130 --> 21:31.422
it's not good news,
I'm afraid.

21:31.506 --> 21:33.923
I've shown that picture
to Alan, to Terry,

21:34.005 --> 21:36.923
to Barry and Leanne,
Carina in the Big House there,

21:37.005 --> 21:39.589
Mimir and Baz.
None of them have seen him.

21:39.673 --> 21:41.381
So you don't think
he's been here?

21:41.714 --> 21:43.798
Like I said,
it's a small island.

21:43.881 --> 21:46.506
If none of them have seen him
then I don't think
he's been here.

21:46.589 --> 21:48.297
♪ ♪

21:48.381 --> 21:50.464
Well, thank you.

21:50.547 --> 21:52.839
-I mean that.
-It's none of my business,

21:52.923 --> 21:55.756
but you seem decent.

21:55.839 --> 21:57.422
Like you deserve decent.

21:58.881 --> 22:01.422
Love is incredible, but...

22:01.506 --> 22:04.089
it can blind us to
a person's faults.

22:04.881 --> 22:07.964
Maybe just better
for you to head home.

22:08.047 --> 22:09.589
Thank you for your help.

22:22.923 --> 22:23.923
(sighs)

22:24.923 --> 22:27.923
(muffled chatter)

22:31.297 --> 22:34.297
Alan:
It's completely mad.
They want you in there.

22:34.381 --> 22:37.005
(fire crackling)

22:37.089 --> 22:39.631
(chatter continues)

22:42.714 --> 22:44.881
-She's not out there.
-She must be out there.

22:44.964 --> 22:46.297
She's having a fuckin' baby.

22:46.381 --> 22:48.130
Tomo:
She's not out there I said!

22:48.214 --> 22:51.130
-So do we call the police?
-The fuck are you talking about?

22:51.214 --> 22:54.130
-Did she say anything, Jay?
-No. She asked me
to get some ice,

22:54.214 --> 22:55.839
and when I came back,
she was gone.

22:55.923 --> 22:58.547
-Is she gonna be okay?
-Helen: No.

22:58.631 --> 23:00.339
She's in active labor.
She's not gonna be okay

23:00.422 --> 23:02.381
unless you find her!

23:02.464 --> 23:04.589
♪ ♪

23:05.756 --> 23:08.506
Listen, we are organizing
search parties.

23:08.589 --> 23:11.214
-Will you help us?
-(indistinct chatter)

23:11.297 --> 23:13.547
Causeway closes in an hour.

23:13.631 --> 23:15.422
Jess trusts you now.

23:15.506 --> 23:17.589
Maybe more
than any of us.

23:19.089 --> 23:21.547
Okay, but we're gone
in one hour, alright?

23:21.631 --> 23:24.547
And look, she doesn't
need stress and fear,

23:24.631 --> 23:27.422
so shotguns
and whatever the fuck
these things are, are out.

23:27.506 --> 23:30.339
She's exhausted
and she's not thinking right.

23:30.422 --> 23:33.089
-She needs help, not weapons.
-What's going on?

23:34.464 --> 23:37.506
-I need to help them search.
-Can we come with you?

23:37.589 --> 23:40.881
-Out there?
But it's bloody freezing.
-Cowboy: Don't worry.

23:40.964 --> 23:43.714
We'll search the Seabird.
It's nice and warm in there.

23:43.798 --> 23:45.547
Tell you what.
Me, your mom,

23:45.631 --> 23:47.297
and your sister can
do the upstairs.

23:47.381 --> 23:50.255
-You can do
the haunted basement.
-You're not funny, you know.

23:50.339 --> 23:52.923
I think I am.
I'll wait for you.

23:53.005 --> 23:56.047
-(door opens)
-(indistinct chatter)

24:06.673 --> 24:08.255
(both sigh)

24:08.339 --> 24:11.297
♪ ♪

24:11.381 --> 24:12.964
(trunk shuts)

24:15.047 --> 24:18.547
Helen:
Ellie, take your sister upstairs
to the room and wait for me.

24:18.631 --> 24:19.756
Is your phone charged?

24:19.839 --> 24:21.839
-Ellie: Yeah.
-Helen: Okay.

24:22.673 --> 24:25.089
Lu? You okay?

24:25.172 --> 24:26.714
Yeah, I'm fine.

24:27.714 --> 24:29.422
Helen:
Don't talk to anyone.

24:29.506 --> 24:30.964
If anything strange happens,

24:31.047 --> 24:32.506
if anyone even
knocks on the door,

24:32.589 --> 24:34.005
you call me
straight away, okay?

24:34.089 --> 24:36.172
-Okay.
-Alright, go on.

24:39.714 --> 24:42.756
(indistinct chatter)

24:47.172 --> 24:48.714
Sorry about yesterday.

24:49.673 --> 24:51.255
It wasn't you.
It wasn't...

24:51.881 --> 24:53.255
you know...

24:54.756 --> 24:56.798
(sighs)
I-I just wanted you

24:56.881 --> 24:58.506
to know that me
and my mom, we're not--

24:58.589 --> 25:00.798
You're not racists,
I get it.

25:00.881 --> 25:03.297
You're just people who turn
a woman and her children away

25:03.381 --> 25:04.964
on the coldest
day of the year,

25:05.047 --> 25:07.589
but you do it regardless
of the color of their skin.

25:09.089 --> 25:10.839
I'm... I'm sorry.

25:10.923 --> 25:13.714
♪ ♪

25:13.798 --> 25:15.673
You didn't see him then?

25:15.756 --> 25:18.297
-Who?
-My husband.

25:18.381 --> 25:19.714
Uh...

25:19.798 --> 25:23.130
Mr. Martin, he said he
showed you his picture.

25:23.214 --> 25:25.297
-He did, right?
-Oh...

25:25.381 --> 25:26.881
That's right, he did!

25:26.964 --> 25:29.047
He showed me his, um...

25:30.089 --> 25:31.422
(rubs hands together)

25:32.422 --> 25:34.589
I haven't seen him.

25:39.297 --> 25:40.506
Alright?

25:40.589 --> 25:43.631
(indistinct chatter)

25:46.422 --> 25:47.756
Cowboy:
Let's check the hotel.

25:50.798 --> 25:53.798
(dog barking)

26:01.631 --> 26:03.547
What is all this?

26:03.631 --> 26:06.047
I mean, we're in
a hotel with no guests,

26:06.130 --> 26:08.673
a holiday development
stopped halfway through.

26:09.631 --> 26:11.839
And when I tried to stay,

26:11.923 --> 26:13.381
they wouldn't let me.

26:13.464 --> 26:15.589
Like I said,
they're divided.

26:16.464 --> 26:19.881
Some wanna open Osea up,
make a few quid, you know.

26:19.964 --> 26:21.923
Others wanna close it down,

26:22.005 --> 26:24.422
preserve it the way it is.

26:24.506 --> 26:27.673
Just make your fucking
mind up, I say. Come on.

26:33.214 --> 26:36.089
-So what, you're just visiting?
-I come here from time to time,

26:36.172 --> 26:37.756
do a bit of work, you know.

26:37.839 --> 26:40.422
Usually in the winter.
Just to stay,

26:40.506 --> 26:41.964
to replenish me-self.

26:42.047 --> 26:43.422
(shuts door)

26:43.506 --> 26:45.631
-Helen: You're a believer then.
-Nah.

26:45.714 --> 26:48.589
Not like these people, but I do
know when a place is special.

26:48.673 --> 26:50.464
(chuckles)
You're a believer.

26:52.047 --> 26:54.881
Places aren't special.
They're just places.

26:57.547 --> 27:00.631
What about that river where
your son's body was found?

27:01.839 --> 27:04.089
I recognize you.

27:04.172 --> 27:05.673
I remember you from the news.

27:07.506 --> 27:08.964
Not that you were
on it that much.

27:09.047 --> 27:10.798
It were mostly your
husband, but...

27:11.547 --> 27:13.422
your grief...

27:14.756 --> 27:16.047
was quieter.

27:17.381 --> 27:18.756
Do you want an autograph?

27:19.589 --> 27:22.589
Isn't that river special, Helen?

27:22.673 --> 27:24.673
No. It's just a place
with water in it

27:24.756 --> 27:26.339
where a corpse was found.

27:26.422 --> 27:29.130
Does it comfort you to
talk about him like that?

27:29.214 --> 27:31.506
Keep what happened
at arm's length maybe.

27:33.339 --> 27:35.381
You don't know
anything about me.

27:36.255 --> 27:37.964
I know you lost.

27:38.047 --> 27:39.631
I know you lost
your little angel.

27:39.714 --> 27:42.464
Oh, Jesus Christ!

27:42.547 --> 27:44.964
Did you just say angel?

27:45.047 --> 27:47.547
Nathan wasn't
a fucking angel, okay?

27:48.547 --> 27:50.589
Look, I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to--

27:50.673 --> 27:52.756
We would get these cards
with that on.

27:52.839 --> 27:54.631
These idiots who've
never even met us

27:54.714 --> 27:56.964
sending shitty condolence cards.

27:57.047 --> 27:58.464
"You've lost your angel."

27:58.547 --> 27:59.881
"Your angel's up in Heaven."

27:59.964 --> 28:02.464
Nathan wasn't an angel.

28:02.547 --> 28:05.297
He was difficult.
He was a difficult child.

28:05.381 --> 28:07.422
He was angry and violent.

28:09.089 --> 28:11.089
So don't talk like you know us.

28:11.964 --> 28:14.047
(footsteps departing)

28:16.214 --> 28:17.089
(click)

28:18.964 --> 28:21.798
-Cowboy: How did
you deal with that?
-(sighs)

28:21.881 --> 28:23.547
With a difficult child?

28:23.631 --> 28:25.714
I loved him.

28:25.798 --> 28:28.381
That's how I dealt with it.
I just loved him.

28:30.089 --> 28:31.964
(wind blowing)

28:34.589 --> 28:36.631
Cowboy:
How was Nathan difficult?

28:37.798 --> 28:40.047
I don't wanna be rude,
but you can fuck off!

28:40.130 --> 28:42.172
I think you
should tell me.

28:43.589 --> 28:45.422
I think you need to tell me.

28:46.089 --> 28:47.255
Look--

28:47.339 --> 28:49.589
He was a troubled boy, okay?

28:51.130 --> 28:53.714
I loved every hair on his body,
but he wasn't easy,

28:53.798 --> 28:55.631
and I'm not gonna
lie about that.

28:56.339 --> 28:59.130
-But, you're a good mother.
-(scoffs) God...

29:00.089 --> 29:02.422
Where do you get this shit?

29:02.506 --> 29:05.255
These platitudes?

29:05.339 --> 29:06.714
I wasn't a good mother.

29:06.798 --> 29:08.547
I was a mom,
like any other mom,

29:08.631 --> 29:10.631
only I lost my child.

29:12.923 --> 29:14.964
The last time
we spoke, I was...

29:15.798 --> 29:18.089
I was shouting at him,
screaming at him.

29:18.172 --> 29:21.214
-Not screaming, I'm sure--
-I was screaming at him.

29:22.506 --> 29:24.589
What did you
scream at him?

29:24.673 --> 29:27.506
-I'm not telling you that.
-You've not told anyone,
have you?

29:30.673 --> 29:33.005
It's easy to tell me.
I don't matter.

29:39.047 --> 29:40.339
I...

29:43.130 --> 29:45.673
I told him that I wished
that he'd never been born.

29:49.839 --> 29:51.839
That was the last thing
I said to him.

29:52.839 --> 29:54.839
-Did you mean it?
-(scoffs)

29:56.631 --> 29:59.589
I've never meant anything
less in my entire life.

29:59.673 --> 30:02.714
♪ ♪

30:05.756 --> 30:08.047
You haven't been to
a West Indian funeral.

30:11.047 --> 30:13.547
-I beg your pardon?
-I went to one once.

30:14.214 --> 30:15.881
It was incredible.

30:17.673 --> 30:20.339
There's these women,
right, who show up,

30:20.422 --> 30:23.297
and their only job
is to make you cry.

30:23.381 --> 30:25.589
And if they sense that
you're not grieving,

30:25.673 --> 30:28.297
that you're not lettin' it out,
they surround you,

30:28.381 --> 30:30.381
push you and they prod you.

30:31.214 --> 30:33.464
Do whatever it takes
to get you flowing.

30:33.547 --> 30:35.172
Why are you saying this to me?

30:35.255 --> 30:37.339
Grief, Helen.

30:39.214 --> 30:41.255
It's a hole that's
all around you.

30:42.214 --> 30:45.172
A warm, dark emptiness that
you can just fall into.

30:45.255 --> 30:47.881
♪ ♪

30:47.964 --> 30:51.255
-What the fuck are you doing?
-If you pretend it's not there,
it'll devour you.

30:52.547 --> 30:54.339
If you try and fight it,

30:54.422 --> 30:56.964
-it'll engulf you.
-Look, just stop, okay?

30:57.047 --> 30:59.798
You need to run
towards it, Helen!

30:59.881 --> 31:02.297
To the hole that Nathan left.

31:02.381 --> 31:04.214
You have to fall into it, love.

31:04.297 --> 31:07.923
-Let go, so you can move on!
-No!

31:11.923 --> 31:12.839
(grunts)

31:12.923 --> 31:14.756
(gasps)

31:16.589 --> 31:19.214
I think I'm slightly fucked.

31:21.130 --> 31:22.214
(sighs)

31:23.005 --> 31:24.589
(dog barking)

31:34.798 --> 31:37.297
Sorry I said you
were a psycho.

31:40.923 --> 31:42.631
Can I tell you something?

31:44.130 --> 31:45.506
I don't miss Dad.

31:46.798 --> 31:48.673
I don't miss him
being all weird

31:48.756 --> 31:50.798
and making Mom cry.

31:52.589 --> 31:54.923
You're nothing like him.

31:57.756 --> 32:00.798
Anyway, what were you thinking
when you hit that girl?

32:02.964 --> 32:04.297
(sighs)

32:05.506 --> 32:07.047
Um...

32:07.130 --> 32:08.923
I wasn't thinking anything.

32:09.005 --> 32:10.923
You must've been
thinking something.

32:11.005 --> 32:14.047
♪ ♪

32:17.130 --> 32:18.381
I thought...

32:20.005 --> 32:22.047
I wish I didn't have to be me.

32:23.172 --> 32:25.089
You shouldn't
think that.

32:25.172 --> 32:26.714
(sighs)

32:33.631 --> 32:35.172
(ragged sigh)

32:46.839 --> 32:49.923
I'm afraid you find me
rather lessened.

32:51.214 --> 32:52.839
We better get some
coffee inside him.

32:52.923 --> 32:55.005
Mm! Coffee.

32:55.089 --> 32:56.381
Warm.

32:57.506 --> 32:58.756
(sighs)

32:58.839 --> 33:01.631
(Janny mumbling)

33:01.714 --> 33:04.464
-Helen: What about Jess?
-There's people out
there furious with him.

33:04.547 --> 33:07.422
He needs to be sober.
You stay here.

33:07.506 --> 33:09.964
-I'll be back in a sec.
-Wait-wait, I've gotta go.

33:10.047 --> 33:12.297
-I've got 20 minutes
before the...
-Janny: Well, I didn't start it.

33:12.381 --> 33:14.881
-(sighs)
-All this. Not me.

33:16.381 --> 33:18.422
-None of us wanted this.
-(sighs)

33:20.047 --> 33:22.589
-Are you alright?
-(chuckle, gag) Oh!

33:24.214 --> 33:26.130
-I do beg your pardon.
-(sighs)

33:26.214 --> 33:29.881
-It's the stress, the fear...
-Don't worry. I'll clean it up.

33:29.964 --> 33:31.547
I'm so sorry.

33:32.714 --> 33:35.172
Of course, it was Sam
what started all this.

33:35.255 --> 33:36.964
♪ ♪

33:37.047 --> 33:39.339
Oh, such
a pretty boy.

33:39.422 --> 33:42.047
Turns up, this starts...
(scoffs)

33:43.631 --> 33:45.422
Did you just say "Sam"?

33:46.297 --> 33:48.631
-Was Sam here?
-Hm?

33:49.547 --> 33:51.589
It's you! (chuckles)

33:54.130 --> 33:56.214
Is this who you're
talking about?

33:57.255 --> 33:59.881
This man here?
Is this Sam?

34:01.422 --> 34:04.464
You can see it in his eyes.

34:06.089 --> 34:08.089
The darkness.

34:09.756 --> 34:12.714
(tense music playing)

34:12.798 --> 34:14.839
♪ ♪

34:17.130 --> 34:19.130
(panting)

34:21.464 --> 34:23.589
-(door slams)
-You lied.

34:23.673 --> 34:25.923
-I what?
-Sam was here.

34:26.005 --> 34:29.005
-No, no, he wasn't.
-Janny said he was here.

34:29.089 --> 34:31.381
Janny?
What, he's in there, is he?

34:31.464 --> 34:33.923
-That man's a drunk.
-You never asked Alan.

34:34.464 --> 34:36.839
You never asked anyone.
You took that photo,

34:36.923 --> 34:39.506
and you showed no one.

34:39.589 --> 34:41.214
Look, I don't know
what's been said to you--

34:41.297 --> 34:42.714
Look, I'm his wife, alright?

34:42.798 --> 34:45.047
Those are his kids.
Why are you lying?

34:45.130 --> 34:47.089
-I'm not lying--
-Why the fuck are you lying?

34:47.172 --> 34:49.005
Mrs. Martin:
'Course he's lying.

34:50.005 --> 34:53.130
'Course he's fuckin' lyin'.
What else do you
expect him to do?

34:55.005 --> 34:56.631
Sam was here?

34:57.172 --> 34:58.714
He was.

34:58.798 --> 35:00.839
(sniffles) He, uh...

35:03.005 --> 35:05.839
(sighs)
He came around the time
of the festival and...

35:07.005 --> 35:08.756
he got...

35:08.839 --> 35:10.839
all involved in things, and...

35:11.631 --> 35:13.673
people weren't happy with him.

35:14.714 --> 35:16.255
They still aren't.

35:16.339 --> 35:17.881
That's what all this
nonsense is about.

35:19.005 --> 35:20.964
-Is he here now?
-Mrs. Martin: No.

35:22.631 --> 35:24.547
And why should I believe you?

35:24.631 --> 35:27.172
I don't give a shit whether
you believe it or not.

35:28.547 --> 35:30.631
He left us three months ago.

35:31.798 --> 35:34.881
Came into our lives,
stirred up a bunch of shit,

35:35.506 --> 35:37.756
walked out and left us
to pick up the pieces.

35:38.422 --> 35:40.381
You should know what
that feels like.

35:43.589 --> 35:45.964
Why didn't you
tell me the truth?

35:46.047 --> 35:48.756
Oh, Helen,
don't ask me that.

35:48.839 --> 35:51.547
-Why didn't you just say?
-(Mr. Martin sighs)

35:58.339 --> 35:59.881
He was with someone.

36:00.255 --> 36:01.839
Here on Osea.

36:01.923 --> 36:04.089
Another woman.

36:04.172 --> 36:07.506
He, uh...
he fell in love.

36:07.589 --> 36:09.422
Why he didn't call,
why he didn't have

36:09.506 --> 36:11.339
the guts to tell you,
I don't know.

36:12.506 --> 36:15.172
(sighs)
I don't know you.

36:15.255 --> 36:18.964
I know I don't,
but you seem, uh, proper.

36:20.589 --> 36:23.339
You deserve
better than that.

36:23.422 --> 36:25.422
We all deserve
better than that.

36:27.297 --> 36:29.297
Do you know where he went?

36:29.381 --> 36:31.381
Did he say?
Did he tell you?

36:32.255 --> 36:33.464
Mrs. Martin:
Yeah.

36:33.881 --> 36:36.130
He did. He did tell us.

36:38.923 --> 36:40.547
But we don't wanna say.

36:41.255 --> 36:42.798
You don't want to...

36:44.130 --> 36:46.798
Nine months ago,
Sam walked out the door.

36:46.881 --> 36:48.673
He'd taken out loans,
he took out cash,

36:48.756 --> 36:52.172
he got involved
in bribes and all kinds
of crazy illegal stuff.

36:52.255 --> 36:54.881
He is not in his right mind.

36:54.964 --> 36:57.631
He loves those girls,
but he left us in a mess.

36:58.422 --> 37:00.506
He is not well.

37:01.506 --> 37:03.089
And you don't want to say?

37:04.839 --> 37:06.130
(sighs)

37:07.464 --> 37:09.172
He told us...

37:09.255 --> 37:11.339
he was going back to you.

37:12.923 --> 37:14.005
(scoffs)

37:15.130 --> 37:17.798
-To me?
-Mr. Martin: Yeah,
three months ago.

37:19.297 --> 37:21.422
We haven't heard a peep
out of him since.

37:29.756 --> 37:32.798
♪ ♪

37:33.673 --> 37:35.005
(sighs)

37:35.089 --> 37:38.005
Causeway closes in 10 minutes.

37:38.964 --> 37:41.714
Cross it.
Don't look back.

37:43.714 --> 37:46.839
Start a new life and pray
that man never comes into it.

37:51.005 --> 37:52.547
(sighs)

38:04.673 --> 38:05.964
We're going. Come on.

38:06.839 --> 38:08.547
Oh, thank God.

38:08.631 --> 38:10.381
Ellie:
What about the pregnant lady?

38:10.464 --> 38:12.506
They can find her.
We're leaving, come on.

38:19.297 --> 38:20.589
Man:
Jess!

38:23.714 --> 38:25.839
(distant shouting)

38:25.923 --> 38:28.964
♪ ♪

38:29.047 --> 38:31.589
Ellie:
Mom, I want to stay.

38:31.673 --> 38:33.839
This was supposed to be
my birthday surprise.

38:34.673 --> 38:36.422
What happened to
celebrating my birthday?

38:36.506 --> 38:38.506
Get in the fucking car, Ellie.

38:38.589 --> 38:40.673
(distant shouting continues)

38:41.756 --> 38:42.798
(car door slams)

38:42.881 --> 38:44.506
-Man: Jess!
-Woman: Jess!

38:45.172 --> 38:46.506
(starts car)

38:50.172 --> 38:52.714
(slams door, gravel crunching)

38:56.381 --> 38:58.547
("Dog Days Are Over" by
Florence + The Machine playing)

39:02.756 --> 39:05.756
(waves washing ashore)

39:10.631 --> 39:13.839
<i>♪ Happiness hit her ♪</i>

39:13.923 --> 39:15.673
<i>♪ Like a train ♪</i>

39:15.756 --> 39:19.089
<i>♪ On a track ♪</i>

39:19.589 --> 39:22.297
Talulah:
Mom! Stop! It's her!

39:22.381 --> 39:24.756
-It's that pregnant woman!
-What's she doing?

39:25.255 --> 39:27.589
Ellie:
Is she trying to
get into the sea?

39:29.089 --> 39:30.422
(sighs)

39:31.631 --> 39:33.547
Helen: (quietly)
Fuck.

39:34.130 --> 39:35.214
(undoes seatbelt)

39:39.589 --> 39:41.172
Jess!

39:41.255 --> 39:44.089
-Ellie: Mom, she can't hear you.
-Stay with Talulah.

39:44.172 --> 39:45.673
Talulah:
What are you gonna do?

39:45.756 --> 39:47.714
<i>♪ And from it she fled ♪</i>

39:47.798 --> 39:49.506
Jess!

39:49.589 --> 39:52.381
<i>♪ With every bubble ♪</i>

39:52.464 --> 39:54.964
<i>♪ She sank with a drink ♪</i>

39:56.005 --> 39:57.339
Jess!

39:57.422 --> 39:58.547
<i>♪ And washed it away ♪</i>

39:58.631 --> 40:01.339
<i>♪ Down the kitchen sink ♪</i>

40:02.798 --> 40:05.339
-Jess! Jess.
- <i>♪ The dog days are over ♪</i>

40:05.422 --> 40:07.631
Come back. Come back.

40:08.464 --> 40:10.047
No! No, Jess!

40:10.130 --> 40:12.381
<i>♪ The horses are coming ♪</i>

40:12.464 --> 40:16.047
<i>♪ So you better run ♪</i>

40:16.130 --> 40:19.381
<i>♪ Run fast for your mother,</i>
<i>run fast for your father ♪</i>

40:19.464 --> 40:23.047
<i>♪ Run for your children,</i>
<i>for your sisters and brothers♪</i>

40:23.130 --> 40:26.089
<i>♪ Leave all your love</i>
<i>and your longing behind ♪</i>

40:26.172 --> 40:27.923
<i>♪ You can't carry it with you♪</i>

40:28.005 --> 40:29.422
<i>♪ If you want to survive ♪</i>

40:29.506 --> 40:32.756
<i>♪ The dog days are over ♪</i>

40:32.839 --> 40:36.422
<i>♪ The dog days are done ♪</i>

40:36.506 --> 40:38.547
<i>♪ Can't you</i>
<i>hear the horses... ♪</i>

40:38.631 --> 40:41.756
Helen:
I need towels, okay?
Duvets, cushions, whatever.

40:41.839 --> 40:43.130
(Jess panting)

40:45.881 --> 40:47.255
Talulah:
There's a bedroom!

40:47.339 --> 40:50.339
-(song continues playing
on headphones)
-(panting)

40:52.005 --> 40:53.172
Should I get help?

40:54.214 --> 40:56.631
-No. It's too late.
-(Jess gasps)

40:56.714 --> 40:59.089
-Talulah: What do we do?
-Look, just take, um,
Lu next door

40:59.172 --> 41:00.881
to the other hut, alright?
And wait for me there.

41:02.005 --> 41:04.464
-Talulah: Is she gonna be okay?
-Just go with Ellie. Come on.

41:04.547 --> 41:05.756
Jess:
Oh, it's coming.

41:05.839 --> 41:08.172
Will you help me? Oh God!

41:08.255 --> 41:10.339
(wave crashing)

41:12.547 --> 41:15.506
(waves washing ashore)

41:15.589 --> 41:18.172
(birds chirping)

41:25.381 --> 41:26.506
(opens door)

41:28.547 --> 41:30.297
-This is the key...
-(door shuts)

41:30.381 --> 41:32.881
to the place
I told you about.

41:36.047 --> 41:38.214
I... I can't.

41:39.339 --> 41:40.923
My mom said to wait.

41:41.005 --> 41:42.255
What?

41:43.005 --> 41:45.214
With your little
godless sister?

41:46.714 --> 41:48.422
Really?

41:50.130 --> 41:52.214
Too bad, Ellie.

41:53.881 --> 41:55.339
It's too bad.

41:55.422 --> 41:58.422
(waves washing ashore)

42:04.756 --> 42:07.297
(birds chirping)

42:21.923 --> 42:23.756
(screaming)

42:24.422 --> 42:27.422
(straining)

42:30.964 --> 42:33.464
(screaming)

42:34.798 --> 42:36.798
(groaning)

42:38.130 --> 42:40.881
-(heavy breathing)
-(baby crying)

42:40.964 --> 42:43.547
-Jess: Is it okay?
-It is! It is!

42:43.631 --> 42:46.381
-(baby crying)
-(laughing)

42:46.464 --> 42:49.214
It's a girl, Jess. (laughs)

42:49.297 --> 42:51.381
It's a girl, Jess,
it's not a boy.

42:51.464 --> 42:53.923
-Jess: I know.
-(crying)

42:54.005 --> 42:55.714
I know.

42:55.798 --> 42:58.381
(heavy breathing)

42:58.464 --> 43:01.422
♪ ♪

43:01.506 --> 43:04.631
(baby screeching)

43:06.673 --> 43:08.214
(sighing)

43:08.297 --> 43:10.798
(screeching continues)

43:12.381 --> 43:14.964
(baby quiets)

43:16.839 --> 43:19.881
(baby gurgles)

43:22.673 --> 43:24.214
(sighs)

43:25.297 --> 43:27.130
She matters so much.

43:27.214 --> 43:29.297
(crying)

43:37.214 --> 43:39.297
She matters so much.

43:45.839 --> 43:48.756
(serene music playing)

43:48.839 --> 43:50.881
♪ ♪

43:56.339 --> 43:57.381
(puts down kettle)

44:05.381 --> 44:06.714
(puts down spoon)

44:12.506 --> 44:14.255
Here. Tea?

44:14.339 --> 44:15.798
Oh my God, you are so British.

44:15.881 --> 44:17.547
(laughs)
You don't want it then?

44:18.506 --> 44:20.172
(giggles)

44:20.255 --> 44:21.839
-Oh, it's hot.
-(laughs)

44:24.089 --> 44:26.631
Jess:
Mm, that is so good.

44:26.714 --> 44:28.089
Thank you.

44:28.673 --> 44:30.464
For all of this.

44:30.547 --> 44:31.839
You've been incredible.

44:31.923 --> 44:33.506
I'm glad I was here.

44:34.547 --> 44:36.589
(baby fussing)

44:38.047 --> 44:39.881
I'm sorry.

44:39.964 --> 44:41.589
It's okay.

44:44.130 --> 44:47.339
Everything is okay now.

44:47.422 --> 44:48.923
I promise.

44:52.422 --> 44:54.547
Hey, do you know
what the date is today?

44:55.214 --> 44:56.589
It's the 14th.

44:57.089 --> 44:59.547
Her birthday is the 14th.

44:59.631 --> 45:01.506
Three out of three
bang on my due date.

45:01.589 --> 45:03.714
Oh, the 14th's your due date?

45:03.798 --> 45:06.214
Every time I delivered, bang on.

45:06.923 --> 45:08.631
Like a machine.

45:10.964 --> 45:13.464
So, Jason will be pleased
that he has a daughter?

45:13.547 --> 45:15.881
Oh God, no. (chuckles)

45:15.964 --> 45:17.756
Jason isn't the father.

45:18.130 --> 45:19.255
Right? I-I thought that--

45:19.339 --> 45:22.172
No, her father's name is Sam.

45:24.005 --> 45:26.506
-(giggles)
-Sam, really?

45:26.589 --> 45:28.756
♪ ♪

45:28.839 --> 45:32.047
It was just this crazy
one-night thing.

45:32.130 --> 45:33.798
Just happened.

45:34.964 --> 45:37.130
I'm so glad it did.

45:39.130 --> 45:40.422
It was meant.

45:43.297 --> 45:46.422
It probably sounds crazy to you,
but I truly believe it.

45:50.464 --> 45:52.172
This little girl...

45:52.756 --> 45:55.089
was meant to be here right now.

45:57.798 --> 46:00.130
She's so, so important.

46:01.506 --> 46:02.798
(sighs)

46:09.297 --> 46:11.339
Would you mind
getting him for me?

46:12.673 --> 46:14.422
He's here?

46:14.506 --> 46:15.756
-He's on Osea?
-Oh yeah.

46:15.839 --> 46:17.964
He's in the Big House.

46:18.047 --> 46:19.297
We haven't been talking lately

46:19.381 --> 46:21.881
because of everything
that's been going on.

46:21.964 --> 46:24.506
But I want him to see her.

46:24.964 --> 46:28.005
I want him to look
into her eyes.

46:28.839 --> 46:30.839
Then he'll get it.

46:31.881 --> 46:34.089
Where's the Big House?

46:34.172 --> 46:37.214
♪ ♪

46:41.547 --> 46:43.589
(soft clacking)

46:56.047 --> 46:58.214
-There you are.
-What happened?

46:58.881 --> 47:01.464
Everything's fine.
She's had the baby,

47:01.547 --> 47:03.631
but I need you two to go
and stay with her.

47:03.714 --> 47:06.297
Talulah:
What? (scoffs) Why?

47:06.381 --> 47:07.923
I have to do something.

47:08.005 --> 47:09.964
Ellie, make sure
she's warm and hydrated,

47:10.047 --> 47:12.464
and if there are any problems,
you call me straight away.

47:12.547 --> 47:13.881
And look...

47:14.673 --> 47:16.589
don't tell her anything
about yourselves.

47:17.547 --> 47:19.089
Why not?

47:20.089 --> 47:22.714
She's-- she's in
an odd place, and I...

47:23.631 --> 47:27.214
Look, it's all fine.
Just don't tell her
about us, alright?

47:28.381 --> 47:30.923
I need to do this one thing,
and then we're leaving.

47:33.547 --> 47:36.589
♪ ♪

47:41.589 --> 47:45.047
(waves washing ashore)

47:52.589 --> 47:55.422
-Lu? Lu!
-(sighs)

47:57.255 --> 47:59.297
Um, take my phone.

47:59.381 --> 48:01.547
You just need to stay here
and make sure she's okay.

48:01.631 --> 48:03.714
But Mom said
for you to do it.

48:03.798 --> 48:05.881
If there's any
problems, call Mom.

48:05.964 --> 48:07.589
Ellie, I'm 9!

48:08.297 --> 48:10.714
She's fine.
She just needs her rest.

48:10.798 --> 48:12.798
Yeah, but what about me?

48:14.089 --> 48:16.756
♪ ♪

48:34.464 --> 48:37.255
-(shuts door)
-Jess: Hi.

48:37.339 --> 48:39.172
What's your name?

48:39.964 --> 48:42.756
Talulah.
My mom calls me Lu.

48:42.839 --> 48:44.089
God, I love that.

48:45.464 --> 48:47.089
Is your sister with you?
I thought she--

48:47.172 --> 48:48.798
No.

48:48.881 --> 48:50.172
(sighs) Only me.

48:51.673 --> 48:53.673
Well, it's nice to meet you, Lu.

48:55.172 --> 48:58.005
Wanna come and see the newest
person in the whole wide world?

49:01.172 --> 49:02.756
(chuckles) It's okay.

49:02.839 --> 49:04.631
You can't hurt her.

49:09.130 --> 49:12.089
(dramatic music playing)

49:12.172 --> 49:14.172
♪ ♪

49:16.547 --> 49:17.839
Come on.

49:50.547 --> 49:53.589
(lock clicking)

49:56.172 --> 49:58.130
Kail:
You ready?

49:58.214 --> 50:00.214
(water dripping)

50:02.589 --> 50:04.839
(unlocks door)

50:05.756 --> 50:07.756
(creaking)

50:07.839 --> 50:09.923
(water dripping)

50:20.255 --> 50:23.172
(dripping continues)

50:23.255 --> 50:26.297
-(footsteps)
-(heavy breathing)

51:08.839 --> 51:11.923
♪ ♪

51:38.339 --> 51:40.047
Ellie:
What is this place?

51:40.130 --> 51:43.547
Kail:
They came here to worship
when they were persecuted.

51:43.631 --> 51:46.839
The people who believed
what we believe.

51:47.714 --> 51:49.839
(water dripping)

51:50.547 --> 51:54.005
Salt and soil, Ellie.
Do you understand that yet?

51:55.339 --> 51:58.130
Osea needs to be in balance.

51:58.214 --> 52:00.673
And when it isn't, well...

52:01.631 --> 52:04.339
the balance of the whole
world is thrown out.

52:07.130 --> 52:11.381
These children were
killed on Osea in 535 AD.

52:14.047 --> 52:17.297
There were floods...

52:17.381 --> 52:19.881
worldwide that year.

52:23.881 --> 52:26.881
991,
the battle of Maldon.

52:27.881 --> 52:31.547
A massacre right here
on Osea.

52:33.047 --> 52:35.547
Also the start of
the medieval war period.

52:37.172 --> 52:39.422
The hottest temperatures in...

52:39.506 --> 52:42.214
thousands of years.
You can look it up.

52:43.547 --> 52:45.631
And in 1888,

52:45.714 --> 52:48.673
Frederick Nicholas Charrington,

52:48.756 --> 52:50.756
the man who started all this,

52:50.839 --> 52:53.964
stalked the streets of London

52:54.047 --> 52:55.673
as Jack the Ripper.

52:56.881 --> 53:00.130
Cutting women open.

53:02.255 --> 53:04.881
Snowed in the middle
of summer that year.

53:05.923 --> 53:08.964
So, that means what?

53:10.756 --> 53:13.172
This place is dangerous?

53:13.255 --> 53:14.839
No. No...

53:14.923 --> 53:16.506
♪ ♪

53:16.589 --> 53:18.798
It means it needs
to be loved. See,

53:18.881 --> 53:22.297
people like your mom,
they'll never get it.

53:22.381 --> 53:24.214
She can't feel it.

53:24.297 --> 53:26.255
But, you...

53:27.255 --> 53:28.798
I think...

53:29.631 --> 53:31.714
you can love Osea.

53:32.631 --> 53:34.923
And, if you do,

53:36.464 --> 53:39.297
it will understand you, Ellie.

53:43.297 --> 53:45.964
It will know you...

53:47.297 --> 53:48.964
and it will love you back.

53:51.673 --> 53:54.756
♪ ♪

54:04.464 --> 54:06.506
Isn't she beautiful?

54:07.673 --> 54:10.339
-Yeah, she's amazing.
-Yeah!

54:11.756 --> 54:13.798
Did it hurt?

54:14.339 --> 54:16.255
Yes, it did.

54:16.339 --> 54:18.631
But, it's a good hurt.

54:19.673 --> 54:21.255
Kinda like a...

54:21.339 --> 54:23.964
-it's kinda like
a strange pressure.
-(baby fussing)

54:24.047 --> 54:26.214
At any rate, even when it hurts,
you know you're bringing

54:26.297 --> 54:28.839
something incredible
into the world.

54:31.506 --> 54:34.130
-Can I touch her?
-Yeah.

54:35.631 --> 54:37.756
You can hold her
little hand. Oof.

54:37.839 --> 54:39.047
(baby fussing)

54:39.130 --> 54:40.673
(muttering)

54:45.130 --> 54:47.506
Well you made a person.

54:48.506 --> 54:50.839
Yeah. Most women do it.

54:51.506 --> 54:53.339
You might do it one day.

54:54.047 --> 54:57.714
Your mom did it twice.
Once for you,
once for your sister.

54:57.798 --> 55:00.589
Well, three times actually.

55:00.673 --> 55:02.798
-Three?
-Yeah.

55:02.881 --> 55:05.547
We had a brother, Nathan.

55:09.923 --> 55:11.506
I didn't know you had a brother.

55:12.381 --> 55:14.422
Yeah, we had a brother.

55:15.339 --> 55:17.798
You say his name was...

55:17.881 --> 55:19.047
Nathan.

55:20.506 --> 55:22.547
Yeah...

55:23.214 --> 55:26.214
♪ ♪

55:32.172 --> 55:34.130
Do you want some tea?

55:34.214 --> 55:35.339
Tea?

55:35.422 --> 55:38.214
Don't you think you're a little
young to be making tea?

55:39.047 --> 55:41.839
Or water.
I could get you some water.

55:44.214 --> 55:46.547
Yeah, get me some water.

55:46.631 --> 55:47.923
No.

55:48.714 --> 55:50.255
It's in the back.

55:58.589 --> 56:00.255
Didn't know you
had a brother.

56:05.422 --> 56:07.297
Talulah:
Yeah.

56:19.297 --> 56:22.005
♪ ♪

56:22.089 --> 56:23.631
Where is he, Lu?

56:24.464 --> 56:25.631
Where's Nathan?

56:27.297 --> 56:29.756
We don't like to
talk about that.

56:30.506 --> 56:32.506
This your phone?

56:32.589 --> 56:34.130
Mm-hmm.

56:35.005 --> 56:36.339
You don't need it, do you?

56:37.964 --> 56:39.297
Mm-mmm.

56:44.631 --> 56:47.631
-Can I have water?
-Of course.

56:52.839 --> 56:53.881
(metal scrapes)

56:53.964 --> 56:55.631
♪ ♪

57:06.464 --> 57:08.881
You know this little girl, Lu?

57:09.673 --> 57:11.714
She's gonna lead us.

57:12.714 --> 57:14.714
And there has been a lot of talk

57:14.798 --> 57:16.255
about who should do that,

57:16.339 --> 57:18.631
and a lot of bad ideas,

57:18.714 --> 57:22.172
and all that's done
is make things worse.

57:23.172 --> 57:25.172
But she's here now.

57:25.881 --> 57:28.381
And it is so important

57:28.464 --> 57:31.255
that she is allowed to grow up,

57:31.339 --> 57:33.756
and take her proper place,

57:33.839 --> 57:36.089
with no stupid questions.

57:36.172 --> 57:39.714
-Do you understand that?
-I don't know
about those things.

57:41.172 --> 57:43.005
I'm gonna need you
to sit down now.

57:48.547 --> 57:50.589
